'''giga-'''

#In the [[International System of Units]] and other [[metric]] systems of units, multiplying the [[unit]] to which it is attached by 10<sup>9</sup>. Symbol: G
# (''computing'') Multiplying the unit to which it is attached by 2<sup>30</sup> or 1,073,741,824
# (''computing-marketing'') Multiplying the unit to which it is attached by 2<sup>10</sup>*10<sup>6</sup> or 1,024,000,000 (makes things look bigger)


====Etymology====
From {{Gr.}} ''gigas'', giant

